name: Rob: EXC_BAD_ACCESS (@RobW@iosdev.space)
summary:
Attached: 1 image

I’m painfully white. But for a white person I have very dark skin.
Recently we were having a family conversation about how I *always* get stopped at airport security. My mum said ‘it’s because of the colour of your skin’.
The thought had never crossed my mind before, and I honestly don’t think my skin is that dark, I’m firmly on the border between ‘okay’ and ‘not okay’ on the family guy meme.
Maybe I’m giving airport security too much credit.
